HEADWORD: Colorado
<hw>Col`o*ra"do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Sp., red.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Reddish; -- often used in proper names of rivers or
creeks.</def> <mark>[Southwestern U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Medium in color and strength; -- said of
cigars.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colorado beetle</ent>⟦br⟧
